<paragraph blockId="12.[189,1398,1929,2027]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
Another species described by Smith entirely based on Hardwicke’s drawings is 
<taxonomicName box="[1155,1329,1929,1955]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Dilleniaceae" genus="Dillenia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Dilleniales" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="aurea">
<emphasis box="[1155,1329,1929,1955]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Dillenia aurea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This was not found by Hardwicke on the expedition to Srinagar, but came from much further east, probably in what is now 
<collectingCountry box="[368,509,2001,2027]" name="Bangladesh" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Bangladesh</collectingCountry>
. There are drawings in the British Library collection (Vol. XVI, nos. 70 and
